race.comment: Tricky. BREAKAWAY WEEK (2) resumes in easier for the Kirkup yard in Canberra and has won 2/5 fresh. Delivered this track/trip here first-up last preparation in a 58 and is well placed with the 2kg claim. The betting will be key. SINGLE BEAT (7) had been knocking on the door in Canberra before a plainer effort there last time from a wide gate. Placed her only start here and can get back on track. JUST ONE LOOK (5) progressed nicely last start to finish a close second over 1400m at Mudgee. Showed more like his best form, and Heywood's booking suggests he's pleasing. FANCY GARTER (3) stepping out at this track for the first time. Last appeared when she finished eighth over 1400m at Hawkesbury on October 28. Should be around the mark.
